The quota system was abolished today after 30 years . 
  It will allow dairy farmers to produce as much milk as they like without suffering a financial penalty . 
  Move is expected to drive a spike in production in countries like Ireland, Germany and the Netherlands . 
  Price war over cost of milk is likely to break out, bringing down the price for consumers . 
  British farmers are likely to find the price they are paid by supermarkets is driven down . 
 